<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-567-986  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 567 986.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Engineering  Nov 1990 v9 n11 p147(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Make way for multibody system analysis. (Floating Point) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McGuan, Shawn.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Multibody System Analysis (MSA) embodies the disciplines ofkinematics, dynamics, mechanical analysis and linkage analysis.andO;MSA is the study of mechanical systems made up of components thatgo through large displacement motion including rotation.andP;  MSA iseasily confused with finite-element analysis (FEA), however FEA islimited to analysis of small displacement motions.andP;  MSA programshelp solve difficult nonlinear equations, however the software isnot cumbersome.andP;  Modeling with MSA is straightforward andintuitive, whereas describing a model with FEA involves a lot ofabstraction.andP;  Research and development efforts at MechanicalDynamics Inc focuses on integration and complementarytechnologies, program robustness, and increased applicability.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mechanical Dynamics Inc. (Research).andO;Topic:     Computer-Aided EngineeringResearch and DevelopmentSimulationMechanical EngineeringSystems AnalysisSystems TheoryNew TechniqueKinematicsSoftware PackagesModeling.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>